title: GIS Data & Maps (ESRI) -- Europe, World (CD1)
description:
.shp, .lyr, .tif

.shp can be viewed with most free GIS programs, including qgis, www.qgis.org, .lyr is proprietary and can only be viewed (as far as i know) with ESRI software, their free viewer (ArcExplorer) cannot view .lyr.  .lyr\&#039;s main purpose is to hold metadata, such as color and labels, so there is no info in them that is different than the info in the shapefiles.
